Problem happening now

Flow in your system:

Unverified user tries to login

Your system checks → status != verified

You show error "please verify account"

But before the status check, you already created the session for the user.

So the system thinks:

User already logged in

Then when you open Admin Login, your middleware says:

User already logged in

So admin cannot login.

Correct Login Flow (Important)

You must check status BEFORE creating session.

Correct order
1. Check email & password
2. Check status
3. If verified → create session
4. If unverified → show error (NO SESSION)


Correct User Login Controller Example


public function login(Request $request)
{
    $credentials = $request->only('email','password');

    if(Auth::attempt($credentials))
    {
        $user = Auth::user();

        // check verification
        if($user->status != 1)
        {
            Auth::logout(); // VERY IMPORTANT
            return back()->with('error','Admin must verify your account');
        }

        return redirect()->route('user.dashboard');
    }

    return back()->with('error','Invalid Credentials');
}
Important line
Auth::logout();

This removes the session immediately for unverified users.



Admin Login Should Be Separate



Example:

if(Auth::attempt($credentials))
{
    if(Auth::user()->role != 'admin')
    {
        Auth::logout();
        return back()->with('error','Admin login only');
    }

    return redirect()->route('admin.dashboard');
}





Middleware Logic

User middleware:

if(!Auth::check() || Auth::user()->role != 'user'){
return redirect('/login');
}

Admin middleware:

if(!Auth::check() || Auth::user()->role != 'admin'){
return redirect('/admin/login');
}






Final Correct Flow
User
Register
↓
status = 0 (Unverified)
↓
Admin verifies
↓
status = 1
↓
User can login
If Unverified User tries to login
Check credentials
↓
status = 0
↓
Auth::logout()
↓
Show error

Session NOT created.

So admin login works normally.

Your Bug Fix (One Line)

Add this:

Auth::logout();

inside unverified condition.

